Not sure if this is a JDT issue...  Thought it was related to the Platform UI Field Assist functionality; since, the problem appeared at their API level (confirmed with Susan Franklin).  The only thing JDT related we are using is the org.eclipse.jdt.core.search.SearchEngine class to generate proposals under the covers {i.e. Called by:
public IContentProposal[] getProposals(String contents, int position);}

The ECFException constructor may send a null String when creating a new org.eclipse.core.runtime.Status object, which fails an assertion sanity check.

The code below illustrates the problem.

-------------------------------------------------------------

import org.eclipse.ecf.core.util.ECFException;

public class ExceptionThrowTest {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		try {
			throw new ECFException();
		} catch (ECFException e) {
			System.out.println("no problems");
		}
	}

}

This happens in ModleOdaAdapter's updateROMResultSets, the code:
PropertyHandle propHandle = setHandle.getPropertyHandle( OdaDataSetHandle.RESULT_SET_PROP );
propHandle.setValue( null );
for ( int i = 0; i < columns.size( ); i++ )
  propHandle.addItem( columns.get( i ) );
It will also retrieve result set columns from Library even the query text has changed. So caused this odd action.

