Hi,
It would be nice if the implicit behavior described below can be made more explicit using an option at resource save and load. For example by passing an EObjectResolver to the XMLHelper (Resource.load/Resource.save action). This EObjectResolver can then be used to retrieve the request EObject based on the href. This same ObjectResolver could be used to translate the an EReference to a correct href.
It would be nice if the resource load and objectresolver as an option could also handle non-existing references gracefully by setting the EReference to null, if the EReference.ismany then a non-existing reference should not be added to the list. But this is a nice-to-have.

This enhancement can be present twice, my browser crashed when I saved and I could not find the request so I entered it a second time.

gr. Martin

The newsgroup posting which prompted this enhancement request.

BTW, I've been thinking of providing a save option to control XMLHelper's deresolve behavior.  Such an option could provide callbacks that could also be used to do URI substitution similar to what's done below but without changing the referenced resource's actual URI.  Perhaps it's a good idea to open a feature request for such a thing and then I'll outline a design...


